entries.source: Custom CSS file for HTML output
entries.translated: Custom CSS file for HTML output

entries.source: This local CSS file will be read and injected into HTML exports. Use an absolute path or a path relative to the vault.
entries.translated: This local CSS file will be read and injected into HTML exports. Use an absolute path or a path relative to the vault.

entries.source: This applies app & plugin CSS to HTML exports, but the files become a little bigger.
entries.translated: This applies app & plugin CSS to HTML exports, but the files become a little bigger.

entries.source: This controls how [[wiki-links]] are formatted. Doesn't affect HTML output.
entries.translated: This controls how [[wiki-links]] are formatted. Doesn't affect HTML output.

entries.source: Export files from HTML or markdown?
entries.translated: Export files from HTML or markdown?

entries.source: Export from markdown, or from the HTML visible in Obsidian? HTML supports fancy plugin features, markdown supports Pandoc features like citations.
entries.translated: Export from markdown, or from the HTML visible in Obsidian? HTML supports fancy plugin features, markdown supports Pandoc features like citations.

entries.source: Absolute path to an export folder, like 'C:UsersExampleDocuments' or '/home/user/zettelkasten'. If left blank, files are saved next to where they were exported from.
entries.translated: Absolute path to an export folder, like 'C:UsersExampleDocuments' or '/home/user/zettelkasten'. If left blank, files are saved next to where they were exported from.

entries.source: Show Pandoc command line interface commands
entries.translated: Show Pandoc command line interface commands

entries.source: Doesn't apply to HTML exports. Using the CLI will have slightly different results due to how this plugin works.
entries.translated: Doesn't apply to HTML exports. Using the CLI will have slightly different results due to how this plugin works.

entries.source: Optional override for Pandoc's path if you have command not found issues. On Mac/Linux use the output of 'which pandoc' in a terminal; on Windows use the output of 'Get-Command pandoc' in powershell.
entries.translated: Optional override for Pandoc's path if you have command not found issues. On Mac/Linux use the output of 'which pandoc' in a terminal; on Windows use the output of 'Get-Command pandoc' in powershell.

entries.source: Optional override for pdflatex's path. Same as above but with 'which pdflatex'
entries.translated: Optional override for pdflatex's path. Same as above but with 'which pdflatex'

entries.source: Add extra command line arguments so you can use templates or bibliographies. Newlines are turned into spaces
entries.translated: Add extra command line arguments so you can use templates or bibliographies. Newlines are turned into spaces
